@node "Welcome" "Welcome to Bootlogger..."

@{FG SHINE}____________________________________________________________________________@{FG TEXT}
₤₤₤₤₤₤₤₤₤₤₤₤₤₤₤₤₤₤₤₤₤₤₤₤₤₤₤₤₤₤₤₤₤₤₤₤₤₤₤₤₤₤₤₤₤₤₤₤₤₤₤₤₤₤₤₤₤₤₤₤₤₤₤₤₤₤₤₤₤₤₤₤₤₤₤₤
                           Welcome to Bootlogger
@{FG SHINE}____________________________________________________________________________@{FG TEXT}
₤₤₤₤₤₤₤₤₤₤₤₤₤₤₤₤₤₤₤₤₤₤₤₤₤₤₤₤₤₤₤₤₤₤₤₤₤₤₤₤₤₤₤₤₤₤₤₤₤₤₤₤₤₤₤₤₤₤₤₤₤₤₤₤₤₤₤₤₤₤₤₤₤₤₤₤
     Welcome to Bootlogger V1.4 - I coded the orginal Bootlogger after
seeing a version of this type of program produced by someone else and
decided I could make a better version :) This version is around 7k
smaller than the other program and the layout of the Log is much better.

  V1.0, V1.1 & V1.2 where made by me around a year ago but as I lost
the source code I have re-done it!

  Now in version 1.4 I have encluded an option for when you bootup your
computer hold down F10 and it will place a star by that log, if you
do this everytime you will be able to check the ones with the stars 
and know that they are yours, all others will be suspicious ones ;)

Back to the @{" Main Menu " link "Main" }...

@endnode

@node "Install" "Installing Bootlogger..."

@{FG SHINE}____________________________________________________________________________@{FG TEXT}
₤₤₤₤₤₤₤₤₤₤₤₤₤₤₤₤₤₤₤₤₤₤₤₤₤₤₤₤₤₤₤₤₤₤₤₤₤₤₤₤₤₤₤₤₤₤₤₤₤₤₤₤₤₤₤₤₤₤₤₤₤₤₤₤₤₤₤₤₤₤₤₤₤₤₤₤
                         How to install Bootlogger
@{FG SHINE}____________________________________________________________________________@{FG TEXT}
₤₤₤₤₤₤₤₤₤₤₤₤₤₤₤₤₤₤₤₤₤₤₤₤₤₤₤₤₤₤₤₤₤₤₤₤₤₤₤₤₤₤₤₤₤₤₤₤₤₤₤₤₤₤₤₤₤₤₤₤₤₤₤₤₤₤₤₤₤₤₤₤₤₤₤₤

   ñ  Copy the file 'bl' to your C: directory

   ñ  Load up a text editor and open up your S:user-startup

   ñ  At the bottom of this file type C:bl

   ñ  Save the file

   ñ  Reset your computer, vola done! :)

 Now everytime you computer is booted up the exact time and date are
logged to a file bl.log that can be found in your C: directory. If
you move or delete bl.log a new one will be created in the C: directory.
If you hold down F10 upong bootup until everything has stopped loading
it will place a star by that log so you know that it was you who booted
up the computer.

Back to the @{" Main Menu " link "Main" }...

@endnode

